#eNCA's Nqobile Madlala is on the ground for us. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Nehawu President Mike Shingange says Nehawu's planned public service strike will go ahead on Monday. That is despite the department of Public Service and Administration obtaining an interdict to stop the strike. READ: Nehawu public service strike interdicted Wage negotiations broke down last month. The department offered a 4.7% increase while unions are demanding between 10% and 12%. Members of Nehawu are embarking on a strike after rejecting 4.7% increase offer from the government. The union demands 10 to 12% increase. #eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu is on the ground for us.#DStv403